        "created_at": "2020-02-21T21:48:27.368Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is a sane thing to do given the current state of things.  Should FDB locking capability evolve such that specific key ranges are lockable then a restore operation would only lock the range(s) being restored and you would no longer have to set LOCK_AWARE to work with keys outside of those range(s).</p>",
